/-!

# Ideals over a ring

This file defines `Ideal R`, the type of (left) ideals over a ring `R`.
Note that over commutative rings, left ideals and two-sided ideals are equivalent.

## Implementation notes

`Ideal R` is implemented using `Submodule R R`, where `ÔÇó` is interpreted as `*`.

## TODO

Support right ideals, and two-sided ideals over non-commutative rings.
-/


universe u v w

variable {╬▒ : Type u} {╬▓ : Type v} {F : Type w}

open Set Function

open Pointwise

/-- A (left) ideal in a semiring `R` is an additive submonoid `s` such that
`a * b Ôłł s` whenever `b Ôłł s`. If `R` is a ring, then `s` is an additive subgroup. -/
abbrev Ideal (R : Type u) [Semiring R] :=
  Submodule R R

/-- A ring is a principal ideal ring if all (left) ideals are principal. -/
@[mk_iff]
class IsPrincipalIdealRing (R : Type u) [Semiring R] : Prop where
  principal : ÔłÇ S : Ideal R, S.IsPrincipal

attribute [instance] IsPrincipalIdealRing.principal

